Photo shared by The Anxiety Healer on July 19, 2021 tagging @theanxietyhealer. May be an image of text that says 'HEALING TIPS @theanxietyhealer Be prepared: practice, practice, practice. Limit caffeine and sugar intake the day of the performance. Eat a sensible meal a few hours before you are to perform so that you have energy and don't get hungry. Shift the focus off of yourself and your fear to the enjoyment you are providing to the spectators. Close your eyes and imagine the audience laughing and cheering, and you feeling good. Don't focus on what could go wrong. Instead focus on the positive. Visualize your success. Avoid thoughts that oroduce self-doubt. doubt.'.

node.text:
One of my most requested posts 👉 so obviously I needed to repost!
〰️
Do you experience derealization or depersonalization when anxious?
〰️
DEREALIZATION involves feelings of not living in reality or being disconnected from one’s surroundings.
👇
Someone with derealization may experience:
✅Feeling like they’re living in a movie
✅Perceiving their surroundings as blurry or unreal
✅An impaired sense of time, such as feeling like recent events, conversations, or experiences happened in the distant past
✅A sense of “going crazy.”
〰️
DEPERSONALIZATION means feeling detached from one’s body or disconnected from one’s thoughts, feelings, and experiences.
👇
Someone depersonalization may experience:
✅ Feeling as though they are an audience to their thoughts, experiences, and feelings...as if someone else is living their life
✅Feeling mechanical, automated, and robotic, sometimes to the point of feeling like they aren't in control of their own actions
✅Disturbance in self-perception (this may be confusion about one’s personality or physical state of being)
✅Emotional numbness
✅Detachment from and lack of emotion associated with memories, which may cause you to question whether those memories are real or even their own.
〰️
Something that can help when you feel derealization or depersonalization is by practicing grounding techniques that can bring you back into the present moment.
〰️
What helps you when you feel this way? Let other healers know in the comments! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
〰️
If you ever feel like you need a higher level of care, always reach out to a mental health professional!

Do you ever have a horrible panic attack and then it sets you back days? And then takes you even longer to recover?
〰️
SAME! According to HealthyPlace.com...”The after-effects of a panic attack rarely include immediate relief. That’s partly what makes a panic attack so difficult to experience. When the panic attack ends, the after-effects of a panic attack begin. During a panic attack, we undergo a number of frightening physical anxiety symptoms so we have to protect and take care of our mind and body even after the panic subsides.” 
〰️
Panic attacks can be very scary for many of us and can send us into anxiety overdrive...even after the panic attack is over!
〰️
We can feel stressed, uneasy, and fearful of the next attack.
〰️
Prioritizing self-care immediately during the after-effects of a panic attack may help relieve these symptoms and get us back to ourselves as quickly as possible!
〰️
